race.description: Country Music Meeting 15 Nov Mdn Hcp
race.comment: Tricky. MY CROWN (10) is hard fit now and has threatened all preparation. There was only 1.4L in it at Dubbo last time and the on-pacer finds the right race. Wary of HIP HIP OLE (8) on debut. She's up from Queanbeyan with the Canberra trials under the saddle. Keatings sticks from those and respect the stable. LONG TIME LOVERS (9) missed a whisker in a non-TAB at Mudgee showing more like her best form. The gate is awkward but she goes into the trifectas at least. NORTHERN EXPOSURE (2) resumes and went close at Wellington at the back of his previous preparation. Has a wide gate to manage but the 3kg claim is handy and he'll be around the mark if presented on song.
